@page "/column"
<PageTitle>Column - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="column">Column</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Column component renders a column element typically used inside grid or
                flex layouts.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Column&gt;
    Content inside a column.
&lt;/Column&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="parameters">Parameters</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Style</td><td>string?</td><td>Inline styles.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>ChildContent</td><td>RenderFragment</td><td>Column content.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="column-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Column</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Column</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the Column component maps to the col class inside a Bootstrap
                row or grid container. You can control the column width by passing Bootstrap
                responsive column tokens such as col-md-6 or col-lg-4 through the Specialization
                parameter. Bootstrap's twelve-column grid system governs the layout proportions
                at each breakpoint.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="column-daisyui">DaisyUI Column</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Column</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the Column component uses Tailwind's flex or grid column utilities.
                Because DaisyUI is built on Tailwind, column sizing is expressed as Tailwind
                responsive classes such as w-1/2 or basis-1/3. These can be passed through
                the Specialization parameter. DaisyUI does not define a separate column
                component class — it relies entirely on Tailwind's layout utilities.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="column-basecoat">Basecoat Column</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Column</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the Column component is composed from Tailwind utility classes
                for flex or grid child sizing. Basecoat follows the same Tailwind-native approach
                as DaisyUI for column layout. Column width and responsive behavior are controlled
                through Tailwind utility tokens passed via Specialization or Class. The default
                Basecoat column resolves to a standard flex child that fills its available space.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("column", "Column"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("parameters", "Parameters", 2),
    new TocItem("column-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Column", 2),
    new TocItem("column-daisyui", "DaisyUI Column", 2),
    new TocItem("column-basecoat", "Basecoat Column", 2)
])" />

</div>
